The Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria (FAAN) said contrary to the misinformation presently making the rounds online as depicted by some pictures posted suggesting a breakdown in the baggage processing system at the Murtala Muhammed International Airport, Lagos, wishes to inform passengers and the general public that what is going on is a routine maintenance of the conveyor belts. The statement further note that the procedure is in line with our facilities maintenance program, aimed at ensuring optimal performance of the airport’s facilities. “We therefore appeal to our highly esteemed stakeholders to please bear with us, as the maintenance work will soon be completed. FAAN…. Committed to her core values of Safety, Security and Comfort.